        "altText": "Guava Kush 24k Full Melt 75-80% THC - Mohawk Medibles",
        "sku": "N/A",
        "metaDescription": "Guava Kush 24k Full Melt 75-80% THC\n\nIndulge in the pinnacle of premium cannabis with our Premium Blend 24K Full Melt Full Spectrum Hash. 75-80% THC. This exqui",
        "shortDescription": "Guava Kush 24k Full Melt 75-80% THC\n\nIndulge in the pinnacle of premium cannabis with our Premium Blend 24K Full Melt Full Spectrum Hash. 75-80% THC. This exquisite, solventless dry sift is craft...",
        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<div class=\"flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col relative items-end\">\n<div class=\"pt-0\">\n<div class=\"gizmo-bot-avatar flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full\">\n<div><strong>Guava Kush 24k Full Melt 75-80% THC</strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div class=\"relative p-1 rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center bg-token-main-surface-primary text-token-text-primary h-8 w-8\">Indulge in the pinnacle of premium cannabis with our Premium Blend 24K Full Melt Full Spectrum Hash. 75-80% THC. This exquisite, solventless dry sift is crafted with precision, passing through five ultra-fine micron screens to isolate only the purest trichome heads. Designed for connoisseurs who demand the best, it delivers an exceptional, full-melt experience that showcases the true essence of the plant.</div>\n<div>\n<h4><strong>Consuming and Storage Tips:</strong></h4>\n<p>This type of hash can be snaked and mixed with either tobacco or dried cannabis and rolled into a joint.  It can also be used to top off a pipe or bong bowl or can be dabbed like any other concentrate.</p>\n<p>It is best to store in a very cool place or in a fridge in order to make it easier to work with as it tends to be very sticky when warmed and softened.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h4><strong>Strain Description:</strong></h4>\n<div class=\"flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col relative items-end\">\n<div class=\"pt-0\">\n<div class=\"gizmo-bot-avatar flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full\">\n<div><strong>Guava Kush</strong>, a sativa-dominant hybrid, competed in the 2014 Los Angeles Cannabis Cup. With a 35:65 sativa/indica ratio, it offers a balanced high—relaxing, creative, and sometimes sleepy. It may help with chronic pain, insomnia, and anxiety. The flavor is sweet, tropical, and fruity, with a similar aroma. The buds are green with amber hairs and trichomes. THC levels exceed 21%, but it has little CBD, making it unsuitable for conditions like seizures. Found mainly in Los Angeles and Oregon, it’s a unique strain worth trying.</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h2>🌿 A Brief History of Hashish and Its Methods of Consumption</h2>\n<p><strong>Hashish</strong>, often simply called <em>hash</em>, is one of the oldest known cannabis concentrates, with a rich cultural and medicinal history dating back thousands of years.</p>\n<h3>🕰️ Origins and Historical Use</h3>\n<p>The word <em>hashish</em> comes from the Arabic “ḥašīš”, meaning “grass” or “herb”. It is believed to have originated in the <strong>Middle East and Central Asia</strong>, particularly in areas like <strong>Persia (modern-day Iran)</strong>, <strong>India</strong>, and <strong>Afghanistan</strong>, where cannabis was both spiritually and medicinally significant.</p>\n<p>By the <strong>10th century</strong>, hashish was widely consumed throughout the <strong>Islamic world</strong>, especially as smoking tobacco was not yet prevalent. Hashish was popular among <strong>Sufi mystics</strong>, who used it to achieve altered states of consciousness. By the <strong>18th and 19th centuries</strong>, it spread into <strong>Europe</strong>, where it fascinated writers and artists like <strong>Baudelaire</strong> and <strong>Dumas</strong>, especially through the experiments of the Paris-based “Club des Hashischins”.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Modern Ways to Consume Hashish</h3>\n<p>Hashish has evolved in potency and preparation over time, but its consumption methods have remained relatively consistent. Common ways include:</p>\n<h4>1. <strong>Smoking</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Traditional Pipe or Chillum</strong>: Popular in India and the Middle East.</li>\n<li><strong>Rolled with Flower (Spliff or Joint)</strong>: Crumbled into cannabis or tobacco.</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives or Bowl</strong>: Pressed between heated metal and inhaled.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2. <strong>Vaporizing</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Used in modern <strong>dry herb vaporizers</strong> that can reach the right temperature to activate cannabinoids without burning.</li>\n<li>Cleaner and smoother than smoking.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>3. <strong>Dabbing</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>For modern <strong>solvent-extracted or rosin-style hash</strong>, it can be dabbed using a <strong>dab rig</strong>—delivering fast, potent effects.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>4. <strong>Edibles</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Hash can be <strong>decarboxylated</strong> and infused into butter or oil, then used in food.</li>\n<li>Effects are slower but significantly longer-lasting and stronger.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>5. <strong>Topical or Medicinal Use</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>In traditional medicine, hashish was sometimes used in salves or tinctures for pain and inflammation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>🌍 Cultural Legacy</h3>\n<p>Hashish continues to be a staple in <strong>traditional cannabis culture</strong>, especially in countries like <strong>Morocco, Nepal, Lebanon, and India</strong>. With the global cannabis movement evolving, hash is making a modern comeback in dispensaries as a <strong>natural, solventless concentrate</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>In essence</strong>, hashish is not just a product—it’s a historical artifact of how humans have interacted with cannabis for <strong>centuries</strong>. Whether consumed for spiritual insight, relaxation, or wellness, its legacy remains deeply rooted in global cannabis culture.</p>\n</div>\n<p>Purchase our<strong> Guava Kush 24k Full Melt 75-80% THC </strong>today and enjoy high tense flavors and an enjoyable high.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>",
