        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p>**Buy Hashwood Wine Hash online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium artisan hash at an unbeatable $140/oz deal and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing. Order now for discreet delivery of this exclusive, handcrafted concentrate that combines traditional hash-making techniques with bold, wine-inspired flavour profiles. Experience authentic quality from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory.</p>\n<h2>🧬 Hash Profile</h2>\n<h3>Craftsmanship &amp; Production</h3>\n<p>Hashwood Wine Hash is crafted using traditional hand-pressing techniques that preserve the delicate trichomes and aromatic compounds of premium cannabis flower. This artisan hash undergoes careful curing to develop its signature wine-like complexity, creating a smooth, refined concentrate that honours centuries-old hash-making traditions while delivering modern potency standards.</p>\n<h3>Terpene &amp; Flavour Profile</h3>\n<p>The distinctive wine character comes from a rich terpene blend dominated by earthy caryophyllene and sweet myrcene, complemented by subtle notes of limonene that add citrus brightness. This combination creates the hash’s signature woody, smoky profile with unexpected sweet undertones reminiscent of aged wine—a truly sophisticated flavour experience that sets it apart from conventional hash products.</p>\n<h3>Texture &amp; Appearance</h3>\n<p>Hashwood Wine Hash features a dense, pliable texture that’s easy to work with and breaks apart cleanly for various consumption methods. The exterior displays a rich, dark brown colour with subtle reddish hues, while the interior reveals a slightly lighter, resinous consistency. The hash maintains its structure at room temperature but becomes more malleable with gentle hand warmth.</p>\n<h3>Similar Products You Might Enjoy</h3>\n<p>If you appreciate Hashwood Wine Hash, explore other premium concentrates like traditional Lebanese hash, Moroccan blonde hash, or modern bubble hash varieties. Each offers unique flavour profiles and potency levels while maintaining that authentic, old-world hash experience.</p>\n<p>–</p>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a piece the size of a grain of rice (approximately 0.05g). Hash is significantly more potent than flower.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.2g per session, adjusting based on tolerance and desired effects</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.3g per session for seasoned hash consumers</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Smoking with Flower:</strong> Crumble small pieces and mix with cannabis flower in joints, bongs, or pipes for enhanced potency and flavour</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Traditional method using heated butter knives to vaporize small pieces—provides immediate, intense effects</li>\n<li><strong>Pipe or Bong:</strong> Layer small pieces between flower or use a screen to prevent pull-through; lights easily and burns slowly</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use hash-compatible vaporizers at 180-200°C for smooth, flavourful vapour without combustion</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset:</strong> 2-5 minutes when smoked or vaporized</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 20-45 minutes after consumption</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours, with residual effects lasting longer than flower</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Use Cases</h3>\n<p>Hashwood Wine Hash is ideal for evening relaxation, creative sessions, or social gatherings where you want to savour complex flavours. The smooth, woody profile makes it perfect for experienced consumers who appreciate artisan concentrates. Best enjoyed when you have time to fully experience the nuanced effects and sophisticated taste. Not recommended before work, driving, or operating machinery.</p>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Storage Tip:</strong> Keep hash in an airtight container in a cool, dark place. Avoid excessive handling to preserve potency and prevent oil transfer from your hands.</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>What makes Hashwood Wine Hash different from regular hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Hashwood Wine Hash features a unique wine-inspired flavour profile with deep, woody essence and sweet, smoky undertones. It’s crafted using traditional hand-pressing techniques and undergoes special curing to develop its distinctive complexity, setting it apart from standard hash products with its refined, sophisticated taste experience.</p>\n<h3>How potent is Hashwood Wine Hash compared to cannabis flower?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Hash is significantly more concentrated than flower, typically containing 40-60% THC compared to flower’s 15-25%. This means you need much less product to achieve desired effects. Always start with a small amount—a rice grain-sized piece is sufficient for most users, especially those new to hash.</p>\n<h3>Is the $140/oz deal available for Canada-wide shipping?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Mohawk Medibles ships Hashwood Wine Hash across Canada with fast, discreet delivery. Orders placed before 2 PM EST receive same-day processing. All packages arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure your privacy. This exclusive deal offers exceptional value for premium artisan hash.</p>\n<h3>How should I store Hashwood Wine Hash to maintain freshness?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store your hash in an airtight container (glass or silicone works best) in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight and heat sources. Proper storage preserves potency, flavour, and texture for 6-12 months. Avoid refrigeration as temperature fluctuations can affect consistency. Minimize handling to prevent oil transfer from your hands.</p>\n<h3>Can beginners use Hashwood Wine Hash safely?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> While hash is more potent than flower, beginners can safely enjoy it by starting with very small amounts (rice grain size) and waiting 15-20 minutes to assess effects before consuming more. We recommend mixing it with flower rather than smoking it pure. If you’re completely new to cannabis, consider starting with lower-potency flower products first.</p>\n<h3>What’s the best way to break up Hashwood Wine Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Gently warm the hash between your fingers for a few seconds to make it more pliable, then break off small pieces or crumble it as needed. You can also use a clean knife or hash-specific tools. If it’s too firm, briefly warming it near (not on) a light bulb or in your palm makes it easier to work with.</p>\n<h3>Does Hashwood Wine Hash produce a strong smell when consumed?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes, like all cannabis products, hash produces noticeable aroma when burned. The Hashwood Wine Hash has a distinctive woody, earthy scent with sweet undertones. The smell is generally less pungent than some flower strains but still recognizable. Vaporizing produces less odour than smoking, and proper ventilation is always recommended.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
