        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<h2 data-end=\"241\" data-start=\"193\">🟡 <strong data-end=\"239\" data-start=\"198\">AFG Gold Hash – Premium Afghani Resin</strong></h2>\n<p data-end=\"298\" data-start=\"242\"><strong data-end=\"298\" data-start=\"242\">Indica-Dominant • 30–60% THC • Classic Afghan Flavor</strong></p>\n<hr/>\n<p data-end=\"1019\" data-start=\"734\">AFG Gold Hash is crafted using <strong data-end=\"799\" data-start=\"765\">classic Afghani landrace resin</strong>, known worldwide for its strong body effects and traditional flavour.<br data-end=\"872\" data-start=\"869\"/><strong data-end=\"887\" data-start=\"872\">Right away,</strong> you’ll notice the golden-brown tone that sets this hash apart—soft, oily, and easy to work with, just like true Afghan-style resin.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1293\" data-start=\"1021\"><strong data-end=\"1053\" data-start=\"1021\">As you take the first smell,</strong> earthy aromas rise instantly, mixed with a gentle sweetness and a warm spicy undertone.<br data-end=\"1144\" data-start=\"1141\"/><strong data-end=\"1166\" data-start=\"1144\">Then, once heated,</strong> the flavour becomes full and smooth, blending earthy hash notes with a mild sweetness that makes each hit rich and satisfying.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1593\" data-start=\"1295\"><strong data-end=\"1323\" data-start=\"1295\">After your first inhale,</strong> the Indica-dominant effects begin to settle in. A calm wave moves through your body, easing muscles and slowing stress.<br data-end=\"1446\" data-start=\"1443\"/><strong data-end=\"1481\" data-start=\"1446\">As the high continues to build,</strong> the strong THC levels (30–60%) take hold—giving you a heavy, long-lasting body melt and a quiet, peaceful mind.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1725\" data-start=\"1595\">AFG Gold Hash is perfect for smokers who want <strong data-end=\"1710\" data-start=\"1641\">classic flavour, strong relaxation, and true Afghan craftsmanship</strong> in every pull.</p>\n<hr data-end=\"1730\" data-start=\"1727\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1750\" data-start=\"1732\">🔥 <strong data-end=\"1748\" data-start=\"1737\">EFFECTS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"1863\" data-start=\"1751\">\n<li data-end=\"1777\" data-start=\"1751\">\n<p data-end=\"1777\" data-start=\"1753\">Deep Indica relaxation</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1796\" data-start=\"1778\">\n<p data-end=\"1796\" data-start=\"1780\">Warm body calm</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1820\" data-start=\"1797\">\n<p data-end=\"1820\" data-start=\"1799\">Heavy stress relief</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1838\" data-start=\"1821\">\n<p data-end=\"1838\" data-start=\"1823\">Mild euphoria</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1863\" data-start=\"1839\">\n<p data-end=\"1863\" data-start=\"1841\">Long-lasting comfort</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1868\" data-start=\"1865\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1894\" data-start=\"1870\">🌿 <strong data-end=\"1892\" data-start=\"1875\">MAY HELP WITH</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"1983\" data-start=\"1895\">\n<li data-end=\"1905\" data-start=\"1895\">\n<p data-end=\"1905\" data-start=\"1897\">Stress</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1922\" data-start=\"1906\">\n<p data-end=\"1922\" data-start=\"1908\">Chronic pain</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1941\" data-start=\"1923\">\n<p data-end=\"1941\" data-start=\"1925\">Muscle tension</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1954\" data-start=\"1942\">\n<p data-end=\"1954\" data-start=\"1944\">Insomnia</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1966\" data-start=\"1955\">\n<p data-end=\"1966\" data-start=\"1957\">Anxiety</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1983\" data-start=\"1967\">\n<p data-end=\"1983\" data-start=\"1969\">Restlessness</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1988\" data-start=\"1985\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"2008\" data-start=\"1990\">🟡 <strong data-end=\"2006\" data-start=\"1995\">FLAVORS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"2062\" data-start=\"2009\">\n<li data-end=\"2019\" data-start=\"2009\">\n<p data-end=\"2019\" data-start=\"2011\">Earthy</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2029\" data-start=\"2020\">\n<p data-end=\"2029\" data-start=\"2022\">Sweet</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2039\" data-start=\"2030\">\n<p data-end=\"2039\" data-start=\"2032\">Spicy</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2062\" data-start=\"2040\">\n<p data-end=\"2062\" data-start=\"2042\">Classic hash resin</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"2067\" data-start=\"2064\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"2087\" data-start=\"2069\">🌬️ <strong data-end=\"2085\" data-start=\"2075\">AROMAS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"2170\" data-start=\"2088\">\n<li data-end=\"2106\" data-start=\"2088\">\n<p data-end=\"2106\" data-start=\"2090\">Earthy + hashy</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2126\" data-start=\"2107\">\n<p data-end=\"2126\" data-start=\"2109\">Light sweetness</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2141\" data-start=\"2127\">\n<p data-end=\"2141\" data-start=\"2129\">Warm spice</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2170\" data-start=\"2142\">\n<p data-end=\"2170\" data-start=\"2144\">Afghan-style resin scent</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr/>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a rice grain-sized piece (approximately 0.025-0.05g). Hash is significantly more potent than flower.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.2g per session, adjusting based on tolerance and desired effects.</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.3g per session for seasoned concentrate consumers.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Smoking:</strong> Crumble and mix with flower in joints, pipes, or bongs for enhanced potency and traditional experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use hash-compatible vaporizer at 180-210°C for smooth, flavourful vapour with maximum terpene preservation.</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Traditional method heating two knives and pressing hash between them for immediate effects.</li>\n<li><strong>Topping Bowls:</strong> Add small pieces atop flower bowls for elevated potency without altering your regular routine.</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset (Smoking/Vaping):</strong> 2-10 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Onset (Edibles):</strong> 30-120 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 15-45 minutes (inhaled) or 2-4 hours (edibles)</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours (inhaled) or 6-12 hours (edibles)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Hash is significantly more potent than regular flower. Start with minimal amounts and wait to assess effects before consuming more. for experienced users – beginners should start with lower doses or those new to concentrates.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
