        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p>**Buy Zahara Red Lebanese Hash online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this rare and exotic premium concentrate imported directly from Lebanon and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing. Order now for discreet delivery of one of the world’s most sought-after traditional hashish varieties. Experience authentic Middle Eastern craftsmanship with the convenience of secure online ordering from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory.</p>\n<p>–</p>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a rice grain-sized piece (approximately 0.025-0.05g). Red Lebanese hash is potent and best approached with caution if you’re new to concentrates.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.2g per session, adjusting based on tolerance and desired effects.</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.3g per session for seasoned hash consumers.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Traditional Smoking:</strong> Crumble small pieces and mix with tobacco or cannabis flower in joints or pipes. This is the authentic Lebanese method.</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Heat two butter knives and press hash between them, inhaling the vapour through a funnel or bottle.</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use a concentrate-compatible vaporizer at 175-190°C to preserve the complex terpene profile and traditional flavours.</li>\n<li><strong>Topping Bowls:</strong> Add small crumbled pieces atop cannabis flower in pipes or bongs for enhanced potency and flavour.</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset:</strong> 2-10 minutes when smoked or vaporized</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 20-45 minutes after consumption</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours depending on dosage and tolerance</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Use Cases</h3>\n<p>Zahara Red Lebanese Hash is ideal for evening relaxation, social gatherings, or solo contemplation. Its traditional production method creates a smooth, mellow experience perfect for unwinding after a long day. The exotic aromatic profile makes this hash particularly enjoyable for connoisseurs who appreciate authentic, old-world hashish. Best suited for experienced cannabis users who want to explore premium imported concentrates with rich cultural heritage.</p>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> This is a potent traditional hash concentrate. Start with minimal amounts and wait 15-20 minutes to assess effects before consuming more. beginners should start with smaller amounts and lower potency products first.</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>What makes Zahara Red Lebanese Hash different from other hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Zahara Red Lebanese Hash is produced using centuries-old traditional methods in Lebanon’s Bekaa Valley. Unlike modern pressed hash, Red Lebanese is hand-rubbed and naturally aged, giving it a distinctive reddish-brown colour, smooth texture, and complex aromatic profile that’s nearly impossible to replicate elsewhere. This authentic imported hash represents true Middle Eastern craftsmanship.</p>\n<h3>How do I use Red Lebanese Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Red Lebanese Hash is versatile and can be crumbled into joints with flower or tobacco, heated using hot knives, vaporized at 175-190°C, or sprinkled atop bowls. Start with a small rice grain-sized amount if you’re new to hash. The traditional Lebanese method involves mixing it with tobacco in hand-rolled cigarettes.</p>\n<h3>How potent is Zahara Red Lebanese Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Red Lebanese Hash is a potent concentrate with significantly higher THC content than regular cannabis flower. While exact percentages vary by batch, traditional Lebanese hash typically ranges from 30-50% THC. This makes it suitable for experienced users, and beginners should start with very small amounts and wait to assess effects.</p>\n<h3>Is Zahara Red Lebanese Hash suitable for beginners?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> While Red Lebanese Hash offers a smoother experience than many modern concentrates, it’s still quite potent and best suited for those with some cannabis experience. If you’re new to hash, start with a tiny amount (smaller than a grain of rice), wait 15-20 minutes, and increase gradually only if needed. Always consume in a comfortable, safe environment.</p>\n<h3>How should I store Red Lebanese Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store your Zahara Red Lebanese Hash in an airtight container in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight and heat. Parchment paper or glass containers work best. Properly stored hash can maintain its potency and flavour for 6-12 months or longer. Avoid plastic bags for long-term storage as they can affect texture and quality.</p>\n<h3>Does Mohawk Medibles ship Zahara Red Lebanese Hash across Canada?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! We offer fast, discreet Canada-wide shipping of Zahara Red Lebanese Hash with same-day processing on orders placed before 2 PM EST. All packages arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure privacy. This rare imported hash is available for delivery to your door anywhere in Canada.</p>\n<h3>Why is Lebanese hash red in colour?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> The distinctive reddish-brown colour comes from the traditional production process and natural aging. Lebanese farmers hand-rub cannabis plants to collect resin, which is then pressed and aged. The aging process, combined with the specific cannabis varieties grown in Lebanon’s Bekaa Valley and the traditional pressing techniques, creates the characteristic red hue that gives this hash its name and legendary status.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
