        "shortDescription": "🍇 Grape Hash – $5/Gram Special\nIndica-Dominant • Smooth • Sweet + Earthy • THC: 18%–22%\n\nGrape Hash brings you the best of both worlds—sweet grape notes and rich, earthy hash power.Right from the fi...",
        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<h2 data-end=\"218\" data-start=\"179\">🍇 <strong data-end=\"216\" data-start=\"184\">Grape Hash – $5/Gram Special</strong></h2>\n<p data-end=\"264\" data-start=\"219\"><strong data-end=\"264\" data-start=\"219\">Indica-Dominant • Smooth • Sweet + Earthy • THC: 18%–22%</strong></p>\n<hr/>\n<p data-end=\"896\" data-start=\"629\">Grape Hash brings you the best of both worlds—<strong data-end=\"696\" data-start=\"675\">sweet grape notes</strong> and <strong data-end=\"728\" data-start=\"701\">rich, earthy hash power</strong>.<br data-end=\"732\" data-start=\"729\"/><strong data-end=\"763\" data-start=\"732\">Right from the first sniff,</strong> you’ll notice the fruity aroma lifting through the classic hash scent, giving it a smooth and sweet twist that stands out instantly.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1128\" data-start=\"898\"><strong data-end=\"920\" data-start=\"898\">As you crumble it,</strong> the hash releases deeper woody tones, blending perfectly with the grape sweetness.<br data-end=\"1006\" data-start=\"1003\"/><strong data-end=\"1019\" data-start=\"1006\">Once lit,</strong> the flavour becomes even fuller, offering a warm, rustic smoke with a fruity finish that lingers pleasantly.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1420\" data-start=\"1130\"><strong data-end=\"1161\" data-start=\"1130\">Soon after your first pull,</strong> the Indica-leaning effects begin to settle in. A slow body relaxation spreads through your muscles, calming tension and easing stress.<br data-end=\"1299\" data-start=\"1296\"/><strong data-end=\"1322\" data-start=\"1299\">As the high builds,</strong> mental clarity remains steady, allowing you to stay relaxed without feeling foggy or overwhelmed.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1616\" data-start=\"1422\">This makes Grape Hash ideal for evening sessions, movie nights, or unwinding after work—especially if you prefer a <strong data-end=\"1581\" data-start=\"1537\">smooth, flavourful, Backwoods-style hash</strong> with a mellow but satisfying high.</p>\n<hr data-end=\"1621\" data-start=\"1618\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1641\" data-start=\"1623\">🔥 <strong data-end=\"1639\" data-start=\"1628\">EFFECTS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"1740\" data-start=\"1642\">\n<li data-end=\"1666\" data-start=\"1642\">\n<p data-end=\"1666\" data-start=\"1644\">Relaxing body warmth</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1685\" data-start=\"1667\">\n<p data-end=\"1685\" data-start=\"1669\">Calm + clarity</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1703\" data-start=\"1686\">\n<p data-end=\"1703\" data-start=\"1688\">Smooth unwind</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1722\" data-start=\"1704\">\n<p data-end=\"1722\" data-start=\"1706\">Light euphoria</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1740\" data-start=\"1723\">\n<p data-end=\"1740\" data-start=\"1725\">Evening chill</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1745\" data-start=\"1742\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1771\" data-start=\"1747\">🌿 <strong data-end=\"1769\" data-start=\"1752\">MAY HELP WITH</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"1844\" data-start=\"1772\">\n<li data-end=\"1782\" data-start=\"1772\">\n<p data-end=\"1782\" data-start=\"1774\">Stress</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1794\" data-start=\"1783\">\n<p data-end=\"1794\" data-start=\"1785\">Anxiety</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1813\" data-start=\"1795\">\n<p data-end=\"1813\" data-start=\"1797\">Muscle tension</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1827\" data-start=\"1814\">\n<p data-end=\"1827\" data-start=\"1816\">Mild pain</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1844\" data-start=\"1828\">\n<p data-end=\"1844\" data-start=\"1830\">Restlessness</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1849\" data-start=\"1846\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1869\" data-start=\"1851\">🍇 <strong data-end=\"1867\" data-start=\"1856\">FLAVORS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"1922\" data-start=\"1870\">\n<li data-end=\"1885\" data-start=\"1870\">\n<p data-end=\"1885\" data-start=\"1872\">Sweet grape</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1896\" data-start=\"1886\">\n<p data-end=\"1896\" data-start=\"1888\">Earthy</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1906\" data-start=\"1897\">\n<p data-end=\"1906\" data-start=\"1899\">Woody</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1922\" data-start=\"1907\">\n<p data-end=\"1922\" data-start=\"1909\">Smooth hash</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1927\" data-start=\"1924\"/>\n<h3 data-end=\"1947\" data-start=\"1929\">🌬️ <strong data-end=\"1945\" data-start=\"1935\">AROMAS</strong></h3>\n<ul data-end=\"2019\" data-start=\"1948\">\n<li data-end=\"1964\" data-start=\"1948\">\n<p data-end=\"1964\" data-start=\"1950\">Fruity grape</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1979\" data-start=\"1965\">\n<p data-end=\"1979\" data-start=\"1967\">Deep earth</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1996\" data-start=\"1980\">\n<p data-end=\"1996\" data-start=\"1982\">Wood + spice</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"2019\" data-start=\"1997\">\n<p data-end=\"2019\" data-start=\"1999\">Classic hash scent</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr/>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a rice grain-sized piece (approximately 0.025-0.05g). Hash is significantly more potent than flower.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.2g per session, adjusting based on tolerance and desired effects.</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.3g per session for seasoned concentrate consumers.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Smoking:</strong> Crumble and mix with flower in joints, pipes, or bongs for enhanced potency and traditional experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use hash-compatible vaporizer at 180-210°C for smooth, flavourful vapour with maximum terpene preservation.</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Traditional method heating two knives and pressing hash between them for immediate effects.</li>\n<li><strong>Topping Bowls:</strong> Add small pieces atop flower bowls for elevated potency without altering your regular routine.</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset (Smoking/Vaping):</strong> 2-10 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Onset (Edibles):</strong> 30-120 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 15-45 minutes (inhaled) or 2-4 hours (edibles)</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours (inhaled) or 6-12 hours (edibles)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Hash is significantly more potent than regular flower. Start with minimal amounts and wait to assess effects before consuming more. for experienced users – beginners should start with lower doses or those new to concentrates.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
