        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<h1 data-end=\"257\" data-start=\"200\">⚡❄️ <strong data-end=\"255\" data-start=\"206\">Alaskan Thunder Fuck (ATF) – Static Sift Hash</strong></h1>\n<p data-end=\"331\" data-start=\"258\"><strong data-end=\"310\" data-start=\"258\">Sativa Dominant Hybrid – 70% Sativa / 30% Indica</strong><br data-end=\"313\" data-start=\"310\"/><strong data-end=\"331\" data-start=\"313\">THC: 16% – 23%</strong></p>\n<p data-end=\"621\" data-start=\"333\"><strong data-end=\"357\" data-start=\"333\">Alaskan Thunder Fuck</strong>, often referred to as <strong data-end=\"387\" data-start=\"380\">ATF</strong>, is a legendary sativa strain that truly stands out. In this case, it’s been elevated even further through <strong data-end=\"523\" data-start=\"495\">premium static sift hash</strong> production. As a result, you get a solventless concentrate that delivers both purity and potency.</p>\n<p data-end=\"938\" data-start=\"623\">Right away, the experience begins with a <strong data-end=\"687\" data-start=\"664\">fast, cerebral lift</strong>. Almost immediately, your mood rises. At the same time, your thoughts feel lighter. Shortly after, creativity starts to flow, and conversation becomes easier and more natural. Meanwhile, energy levels increase without feeling jittery or overwhelming.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1241\" data-start=\"940\">As the high continues to build, the body remains relaxed yet functional. In contrast to heavier hashes, ATF keeps you alert. Because of this balance, it’s especially well-suited for daytime or early evening sessions. Eventually, appetite stimulation appears, while stress and tension slowly fade away.</p>\n<hr data-end=\"1246\" data-start=\"1243\"/>\n<h2 data-end=\"1273\" data-start=\"1248\">✨ <strong data-end=\"1273\" data-start=\"1253\">What You’ll Feel</strong></h2>\n<ul data-end=\"1428\" data-start=\"1274\">\n<li data-end=\"1302\" data-start=\"1274\">\n<p data-end=\"1302\" data-start=\"1276\">😄 Euphoric and uplifted</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1336\" data-start=\"1303\">\n<p data-end=\"1336\" data-start=\"1305\">🗣️ More talkative and social</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1365\" data-start=\"1337\">\n<p data-end=\"1365\" data-start=\"1339\">🎨 Creative and inspired</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1398\" data-start=\"1366\">\n<p data-end=\"1398\" data-start=\"1368\">⚡ Energized yet clear-headed</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1428\" data-start=\"1399\">\n<p data-end=\"1428\" data-start=\"1401\">🔥 Light arousal and buzz</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1433\" data-start=\"1430\"/>\n<h2 data-end=\"1458\" data-start=\"1435\">🩺 <strong data-end=\"1458\" data-start=\"1441\">May Help With</strong></h2>\n<ul data-end=\"1600\" data-start=\"1459\">\n<li data-end=\"1475\" data-start=\"1459\">\n<p data-end=\"1475\" data-start=\"1461\">Chronic pain</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1501\" data-start=\"1476\">\n<p data-end=\"1501\" data-start=\"1478\">Depression and stress</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1513\" data-start=\"1502\">\n<p data-end=\"1513\" data-start=\"1504\">Fatigue</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1522\" data-start=\"1514\">\n<p data-end=\"1522\" data-start=\"1516\">PTSD</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1550\" data-start=\"1523\">\n<p data-end=\"1550\" data-start=\"1525\">Migraines and headaches</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1579\" data-start=\"1551\">\n<p data-end=\"1579\" data-start=\"1553\">Nausea and appetite loss</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1600\" data-start=\"1580\">\n<p data-end=\"1600\" data-start=\"1582\">Bipolar disorder</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1605\" data-start=\"1602\"/>\n<h2 data-end=\"1630\" data-start=\"1607\">🍊 <strong data-end=\"1630\" data-start=\"1613\">Flavour Notes</strong></h2>\n<ul data-end=\"1680\" data-start=\"1631\">\n<li data-end=\"1641\" data-start=\"1631\">\n<p data-end=\"1641\" data-start=\"1633\">Citrus</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1651\" data-start=\"1642\">\n<p data-end=\"1651\" data-start=\"1644\">Grape</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1660\" data-start=\"1652\">\n<p data-end=\"1660\" data-start=\"1654\">Pine</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1670\" data-start=\"1661\">\n<p data-end=\"1670\" data-start=\"1663\">Sweet</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1680\" data-start=\"1671\">\n<p data-end=\"1680\" data-start=\"1673\">Spicy</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1685\" data-start=\"1682\"/>\n<h2 data-end=\"1711\" data-start=\"1687\">🌬️ <strong data-end=\"1711\" data-start=\"1694\">Aroma Profile</strong></h2>\n<ul data-end=\"1812\" data-start=\"1712\">\n<li data-end=\"1733\" data-start=\"1712\">\n<p data-end=\"1733\" data-start=\"1714\">Earthy base notes</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1762\" data-start=\"1734\">\n<p data-end=\"1762\" data-start=\"1736\">Strong pungent character</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1786\" data-start=\"1763\">\n<p data-end=\"1786\" data-start=\"1765\">Grape-forward tones</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1812\" data-start=\"1787\">\n<p data-end=\"1812\" data-start=\"1789\">Warm spicy undertones</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-end=\"1817\" data-start=\"1814\"/>\n<h2 data-end=\"1862\" data-start=\"1819\">🧊 <strong data-end=\"1862\" data-start=\"1825\">Why Static Sift Hash Is Different</strong></h2>\n<p data-end=\"2194\" data-start=\"1863\">First, the process is <strong data-end=\"1905\" data-start=\"1885\">100% solventless</strong>.<br data-end=\"1909\" data-start=\"1906\"/>Then, static electricity is used to attract pure trichome heads.<br data-end=\"1976\" data-start=\"1973\"/>As a result, plant material is left behind.<br data-end=\"2022\" data-start=\"2019\"/>Because of this, the final product is cleaner.<br data-end=\"2071\" data-start=\"2068\"/>At the same time, flavour and aroma are preserved.<br data-end=\"2124\" data-start=\"2121\"/>Ultimately, this creates a <strong data-end=\"2193\" data-start=\"2151\">smoother, more potent, high-grade hash</strong>.</p>\n<hr/>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a rice grain-sized piece (approximately 0.025-0.05g). Hash is significantly more potent than flower.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.2g per session, adjusting based on tolerance and desired effects.</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.3g per session for seasoned concentrate consumers.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Smoking:</strong> Crumble and mix with flower in joints, pipes, or bongs for enhanced potency and traditional experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use hash-compatible vaporizer at 180-210°C for smooth, flavourful vapour with maximum terpene preservation.</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Traditional method heating two knives and pressing hash between them for immediate effects.</li>\n<li><strong>Topping Bowls:</strong> Add small pieces atop flower bowls for elevated potency without altering your regular routine.</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset (Smoking/Vaping):</strong> 2-10 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Onset (Edibles):</strong> 30-120 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 15-45 minutes (inhaled) or 2-4 hours (edibles)</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours (inhaled) or 6-12 hours (edibles)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Hash is significantly more potent than regular flower. Start with minimal amounts and wait to assess effects before consuming more. for experienced users – beginners should start with lower doses or those new to concentrates.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
