        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p>**Buy Gevalia Afghan Hash online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this rare, handmade Afghan hash and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing. Order now for discreet delivery of this exotic, tea-infused concentrate sourced using traditional Afghan methods. Experience authentic hash craftsmanship from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory.</p>\n<h2>🧬 Hash Profile</h2>\n<h3>Origin &amp; Traditional Craftsmanship</h3>\n<p>Gevalia Afghan Hash originates from the rugged mountainous regions on the outskirts of Afghanistan, where hash-making traditions span centuries. This artisanal concentrate is handcrafted using time-honoured pressing techniques passed down through generations of Afghan hash makers. The unique infusion of local tea during the pressing process creates a distinctive aromatic signature that sets Gevalia apart from conventional hash products.</p>\n<h3>Terpene &amp; Flavour Profile</h3>\n<p>The traditional tea infusion imparts complex herbal and earthy notes, complemented by the natural terpenes preserved through careful hand-pressing. Expect rich, spicy undertones characteristic of Afghan landraces, with subtle floral hints from the tea integration. The flavour profile is robust and full-bodied, offering a smooth, aromatic smoking experience that reflects its heritage.</p>\n<h3>Texture &amp; Appearance</h3>\n<p>Gevalia Afghan Hash displays the classic dark brown to black colouration typical of premium Afghan concentrates. The texture is pliable when warmed, making it easy to work with for various consumption methods. Hand-pressed consistency ensures even density throughout, with a slightly oily exterior that indicates proper resin content and freshness.</p>\n<h3>Similar Products</h3>\n<p>If you enjoy Gevalia Afghan Hash, explore other traditional concentrates like Moroccan hash, Lebanese blonde hash, or other hand-pressed artisanal varieties. These heritage products offer similar robust flavour profiles and cultural authenticity.</p>\n<p>–</p>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with a match-head sized piece (approximately 0.05-0.1g). Hash is significantly more potent than flower.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.1-0.3g per session, depending on tolerance and desired effects</li>\n<li><strong>High Tolerance:</strong> Up to 0.5g per session for seasoned hash consumers</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Consumption Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Traditional Smoking:</strong> Crumble small pieces and mix with tobacco or cannabis flower in joints or pipes</li>\n<li><strong>Hot Knives:</strong> Classic method using heated butter knives for vaporization (use caution)</li>\n<li><strong>Bong or Pipe:</strong> Place small piece on top of flower bowl, or use dedicated hash screens</li>\n<li><strong>Vaporizing:</strong> Use hash-compatible vaporizers at 180-200°C for smooth, flavourful vapour</li>\n<li><strong>Hookah:</strong> Traditional method using water pipes for cooled, filtered smoke</li>\n<li><strong>Hash Edibles (Advanced):</strong> To make edibles, decarboxylate hash at 110-120°C (230-250°F) for 30-40 minutes to activate THC. Mix into butter or oil-based recipes. Effects take 30-120 minutes and last 6-12 hours. Hash edibles are significantly more potent than flower edibles—start with 1/4 of your normal flower edible dose.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset:</strong> 2-5 minutes when smoked or vaporized</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 20-45 minutes after consumption</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-4 hours depending on dosage and tolerance</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Use Cases</h3>\n<p>Gevalia Afghan Hash is ideal for evening relaxation, meditation, or cultural appreciation of traditional cannabis craftsmanship. The robust, tea-infused flavour profile makes it perfect for experienced consumers seeking authentic hash experiences. Best enjoyed in calm settings where you can appreciate the complex aromatics and deep relaxation effects.</p>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Hash is a concentrated cannabis product with elevated potency compared to flower. Start with minimal amounts and wait 15-20 minutes to assess effects before consuming more. Not recommended for cannabis beginners.</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>What makes Gevalia Afghan Hash unique?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Gevalia Afghan Hash is handmade using traditional Afghan pressing methods and uniquely infused with local tea during production. This creates a distinctive aroma and flavour profile you won’t find in modern concentrates. The artisanal craftsmanship and cultural heritage make it a rare find in the Canadian market.</p>\n<h3>How do I use Gevalia Afghan Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Hash can be crumbled and mixed with flower in joints or pipes, vaporized in compatible devices at 180-200°C, or used with traditional methods like hot knives or hookahs. Warm it slightly between your fingers to make it easier to break apart. Always start with a small amount as hash is more potent than flower.</p>\n<h3>How strong is Afghan hash compared to regular cannabis?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Hash is a concentrated form of cannabis containing significantly higher cannabinoid levels than flower, typically 30-60% THC or higher. Gevalia Afghan Hash delivers potent effects with smaller amounts, making it best suited for experienced consumers. Start with a match-head sized piece if you’re new to hash.</p>\n<h3>How should I store Gevalia Afghan Hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store your hash in an airtight container in a cool, dark place away from heat and moisture. Parchment paper or silicone containers work well to prevent sticking. Properly stored hash can maintain quality for 1-2 years. Avoid refrigeration as condensation can affect texture and potency.</p>\n<h3>Is Gevalia Afghan Hash suitable for beginners?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Due to its concentrated nature and elevated potency, Gevalia Afghan Hash is best suited for experienced cannabis consumers. If you’re new to hash but experienced with flower, start with very small amounts (match-head size) and wait 15-20 minutes to assess effects before consuming more.</p>\n<h3>Does Mohawk Medibles ship Gevalia Afghan Hash across Canada?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! We offer fast, discreet Canada-wide shipping on all our products, including Gevalia Afghan Hash. Orders placed before 2 PM EST are processed the same day. All packages arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure privacy and discretion.</p>\n<h3>What does the tea infusion do to the hash?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> The traditional tea infusion during the hand-pressing process adds unique herbal and floral notes to the hash’s natural earthy flavour profile. This centuries-old Afghan technique enhances the aromatic experience and creates a smoother, more complex taste compared to non-infused hash. It’s a signature characteristic of authentic Gevalia Afghan Hash.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
