        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p>**Buy CBD and THC 1:1 1500MG Tincture online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium full-spectrum tincture crafted by Mohawk Medibles and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing. Order now for discreet delivery of this balanced CBD/THC formula, perfect for therapeutic relief without overwhelming psychoactive effects. Available in Vegetable Glycerin or MCT Oil base to suit your taste preferences.</p>\n<p>–</p>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with 0.25-0.5ml (approximately 5-10mg total cannabinoids). Wait 60-90 minutes to assess effects before increasing.</li>\n<li><strong>Experienced Users:</strong> 0.5-1.0ml per dose (10-20mg total cannabinoids), adjusted based on individual tolerance and desired effects.</li>\n<li><strong>Medical Patients:</strong> Consult with your healthcare provider. Typical therapeutic doses range from 10-30mg total cannabinoids, taken 1-3 times daily.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to Use</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sublingual Method (Recommended):</strong> Place desired amount under your tongue and hold for 60-90 seconds before swallowing. This allows for faster absorption through the mucous membranes.</li>\n<li><strong>Oral Consumption:</strong> Mix into beverages, smoothies, or food. Note that onset will be slower but effects may last longer.</li>\n<li><strong>Consistency is Key:</strong> For chronic conditions, take at the same time daily to maintain steady cannabinoid levels in your system.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset (Sublingual):</strong> 15-45 minutes when held under tongue</li>\n<li><strong>Onset (Oral):</strong> 30-90 minutes when swallowed or mixed with food</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 1-2 hours after consumption</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 4-6 hours of therapeutic effects</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Use Cases</h3>\n<p>This 1:1 CBD/THC ratio is ideal for managing chronic pain, anxiety, PTSD symptoms, and sleep disorders. The balanced formula provides therapeutic relief with mild, manageable psychoactive effects. Perfect for daytime use at lower doses or evening use for deeper relaxation and sleep support. The indica profile enhances the sedative qualities, making it particularly effective for stress relief and promoting restful sleep.</p>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Start with the lowest dose and gradually increase until you find your optimal therapeutic level. Do not drive or operate machinery until you understand how this product affects you. Store in a cool, dark place and keep out of reach of children and pets.</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>What is a 1:1 CBD/THC tincture?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> A 1:1 tincture contains equal parts CBD and THC, providing balanced therapeutic benefits. The CBD moderates the psychoactive effects of THC while both cannabinoids work synergistically to enhance pain relief, reduce inflammation, and promote relaxation. This ratio is ideal for those seeking medical benefits without overwhelming intoxication.</p>\n<h3>What’s the difference between Vegetable Glycerin and MCT Oil bases?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Vegetable Glycerin has a naturally sweet taste and thicker consistency, making it pleasant for those who enjoy a sweeter flavour. MCT Oil (medium-chain triglyceride oil derived from coconut) has a neutral taste and may offer faster absorption. Both are equally effective—choose based on your taste preference and dietary considerations.</p>\n<h3>Will this tincture make me feel high?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes, but the effects are typically mild and manageable due to the balanced CBD/THC ratio. The CBD helps counteract anxiety and paranoia sometimes associated with THC, while the indica profile provides gentle relaxation. At recommended doses, most users experience therapeutic relief with subtle euphoria rather than intense intoxication.</p>\n<h3>How should I store my CBD/THC tincture?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store your tincture in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight and heat sources. A cupboard or drawer works well. Keep the bottle tightly sealed when not in use. Properly stored, tinctures maintain potency for 1-2 years. Refrigeration can extend shelf life but may cause the oil to thicken temporarily.</p>\n<h3>Can I use this tincture for PTSD and anxiety?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Many users report significant relief from PTSD and anxiety symptoms with 1:1 CBD/THC tinctures. The CBD provides anti-anxiety effects while THC helps with intrusive thoughts and hypervigilance. However, this product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Consult with your healthcare provider about incorporating cannabis into your treatment plan.</p>\n<h3>Does Mohawk Medibles ship this tincture across Canada?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! We offer fast, discreet Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing on orders placed before 2 PM EST. Your tincture will arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure privacy. All products are shipped securely and comply with Canadian cannabis regulations.</p>\n<h3>How long will one bottle last?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> This depends on your dosage and frequency of use. If taking 0.5ml twice daily (a common therapeutic dose), a 30ml bottle will last approximately one month. Lower doses will extend the duration, while higher doses or more frequent use will deplete the bottle faster. We recommend starting with one bottle to determine your ideal dosage before stocking up.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
