        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p><strong>19-21% THC</strong></p>\n<p>**Buy Tangie online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium sativa-dominant hybrid and experience the legendary citrus flavour that made Tangie a modern classic. Order now for fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing and discreet delivery straight from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory. Perfect for daytime use, creative sessions, and uplifting your mood naturally.</p>\n<h2>🧬 Strain Profile</h2>\n<h3>Genetics &amp; Lineage</h3>\n<p>Tangie boasts an impressive pedigree as a reimagining of the legendary Tangerine Dream from the 1990s. Bred by DNA Genetics through crossing <strong>California Orange with Skunk #1</strong>, this strain has won multiple Cannabis Cups and earned its place among the most sought-after sativa-dominant hybrids available today. The 70/30 sativa-to-indica ratio delivers the perfect balance of cerebral stimulation and subtle physical relaxation.</p>\n<h3>Dominant Terpenes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Limonene:</strong> Primary terpene responsible for the intense citrus aroma and uplifting, mood-enhancing effects</li>\n<li><strong>Myrcene:</strong> Adds earthy undertones and contributes to the strain’s relaxing qualities</li>\n<li><strong>Caryophyllene:</strong> Provides subtle spicy notes and potential stress-relief properties</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cannabinoid Profile</h3>\n<p>Tangie typically features moderate to high THC levels, making it accessible for both intermediate and experienced consumers. The cannabinoid profile delivers clear-headed effects without overwhelming sedation, ideal for maintaining productivity while enjoying therapeutic benefits.</p>\n<h3>Appearance &amp; Structure</h3>\n<p>Tangie buds are visually striking with vibrant orange pistils weaving through dense, resinous flowers. The nugs display a generous coating of crystalline trichomes that shimmer against the bright green calyxes. The structure is classic sativa—slightly elongated and less compact than indica varieties, with excellent bag appeal that hints at the quality within.</p>\n<h3>Similar Strains</h3>\n<p>If you enjoy Tangie, you might also like: <strong>Tangerine Dream</strong> (its predecessor), <strong>Clementine</strong> (similar citrus profile), <strong>Super Lemon Haze</strong> (energizing citrus sativa), and <strong>Orange Cookies</strong> (citrus with balanced effects).</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>Is Tangie indica, sativa, or hybrid?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Tangie is a sativa-dominant hybrid with a 70% sativa / 30% indica ratio. This means you’ll experience primarily uplifting, energizing effects with a subtle body relaxation that keeps you grounded without causing sedation.</p>\n<h3>What are the effects of Tangie?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Users report clear-headed euphoria, enhanced creativity, improved focus, and elevated mood. Tangie is known for delivering energizing effects that boost motivation and sociability while maintaining mental clarity. It’s commonly used for daytime stress relief, creative work, and social activities.</p>\n<h3>What does Tangie taste like?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Tangie is famous for its intense citrus flavour profile dominated by sweet orange and tangerine notes. You’ll experience a burst of fresh citrus zest on the inhale with subtle earthy undertones on the exhale. The taste is often described as remarkably similar to peeling a fresh tangerine.</p>\n<h3>How should I store Tangie to preserve freshness?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store Tangie in an airtight glass jar or container in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight and heat sources. Proper storage preserves the vibrant terpene profile and potency for 6-12 months. Consider using humidity packs (62% RH) to maintain optimal moisture levels and prevent your flower from drying out.</p>\n<h3>Does Mohawk Medibles ship Tangie across Canada?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! We offer fast, discreet Canada-wide shipping on all our products, including Tangie. Orders placed before 2 PM EST are processed the same day. All packages arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure your privacy, shipped directly from our location in Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory.</p>\n<h3>Why is Tangie so popular?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Tangie has earned its reputation through an unbeatable combination of exceptional citrus flavour, reliable uplifting effects, and award-winning genetics. It’s won multiple Cannabis Cup awards and remains a favourite among both recreational users seeking daytime energy and medical patients looking for mood enhancement without sedation.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n</div>",
