        "metaDescription": "**Buy CBD Full Spectrum Tincture online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium 1000mg CBD tincture",
        "shortDescription": "**Buy CBD Full Spectrum Tincture online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium 1000mg CBD tincture and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping w...",
        "descriptionHTML": "<div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-description\">\n<div class=\"detail-tab-desc detail-content-wrap\">\n<p>**Buy CBD Full Spectrum Tincture online in Canada at Mohawk Medibles**, your trusted Indigenous-owned cannabis dispensary. Shop this premium 1000mg CBD tincture and enjoy fast Canada-wide shipping with same-day processing. Order now for discreet delivery from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory. Available in Vegetable Glycerin or MCT Oil base, this full spectrum tincture provides natural relief without psychoactive effects. Perfect for managing chronic discomfort and supporting overall wellness.</p>\n<p>–</p>\n<h2>💡 Usage Guide</h2>\n<h3>Recommended Dosage</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Start with 0.25ml (quarter dropper) once daily, containing approximately 8mg CBD. Wait 2-3 days to assess effects before increasing.</li>\n<li><strong>General Wellness:</strong> 0.5ml (half dropper) 1-2 times daily, providing 16-17mg CBD per dose.</li>\n<li><strong>Chronic Discomfort:</strong> 0.75-1ml (three-quarters to full dropper) 2-3 times daily, delivering 25-33mg CBD per dose. Consult with a healthcare provider for personalized guidance.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to Use</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sublingual Method (Recommended):</strong> Place desired amount under your tongue and hold for 60-90 seconds before swallowing. This allows for faster absorption through the mucous membranes.</li>\n<li><strong>Direct Consumption:</strong> Swallow directly or mix into beverages. Note that onset time will be longer with this method.</li>\n<li><strong>Consistency is Key:</strong> Take at the same time each day for best results. Full spectrum CBD works best with regular, consistent use.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Onset &amp; Duration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Onset:</strong> 15-45 minutes (sublingual), 30-90 minutes (oral consumption)</li>\n<li><strong>Peak Effects:</strong> 1-2 hours after consumption</li>\n<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 4-6 hours of sustained support</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Use Cases</h3>\n<p>Ideal for daily wellness support and managing chronic discomfort from conditions like bursitis, rheumatoid arthritis, sciatica, and hip dysplasia. Non-psychoactive formula is safe for daytime use and won’t interfere with work or daily activities. The full spectrum formulation contains beneficial cannabinoids and terpenes that work together for enhanced effectiveness. Choose Vegetable Glycerin for a naturally sweet taste, or MCT Oil for a neutral flavour profile.</p>\n<p><strong>Storage:</strong> Store in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight. Shake well before each use. Properly stored, tinctures maintain potency for 12-18 months.</p>\n<h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h3>What is full spectrum CBD and how is it different from CBD isolate?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Full spectrum CBD contains all naturally occurring cannabinoids, terpenes, and beneficial compounds from the hemp plant, including trace amounts of THC (less than 0.3%). This creates an “entourage effect” where compounds work together synergistically for enhanced benefits. Unlike CBD isolate which contains only CBD, full spectrum provides more comprehensive wellness support.</p>\n<h3>Will this CBD tincture make me high?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> No, this tincture will not produce psychoactive effects or make you feel “high.” While it contains trace amounts of THC (under 0.3%), this is not enough to cause intoxication. You’ll experience the potential wellness benefits of CBD without any impairment, making it safe for daytime use and before work or activities.</p>\n<h3>How much CBD should I take for chronic pain relief?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> For chronic conditions like arthritis, bursitis, or sciatica, start with 0.5ml (16-17mg CBD) twice daily and gradually increase to 1ml (33mg) 2-3 times daily as needed. Many users find relief at 50-100mg total daily dose. We recommend starting low and increasing slowly over 1-2 weeks while monitoring your response. Consult with a healthcare provider for personalized dosing guidance.</p>\n<h3>What’s the difference between Vegetable Glycerin and MCT Oil base?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Vegetable Glycerin has a naturally sweet taste and thicker consistency, making it pleasant for those who enjoy a hint of sweetness. MCT Oil (Medium Chain Triglyceride oil derived from coconuts) has a neutral taste and may offer slightly better absorption. Both are effective carriers for CBD—choose based on your taste preference and dietary considerations.</p>\n<h3>How should I store my CBD tincture?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Store your tincture in a cool, dark place away from direct sunlight and heat sources. A cupboard or drawer works well. Keep the cap tightly sealed when not in use. Properly stored, your tincture will maintain full potency for 12-18 months. Always shake well before each use to ensure even distribution of CBD.</p>\n<h3>Does Mohawk Medibles ship CBD tinctures across Canada?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! We offer fast, discreet Canada-wide shipping for all our CBD products. Orders placed before 2 PM EST are processed the same day. All packages arrive in plain, unmarked packaging to ensure your privacy. CBD products are legal across Canada, and we’re proud to ship from Tyendinaga Mohawk Territory to customers nationwide.</p>\n<h3>Is this product safe to use with other medications?</h3>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> While CBD is generally well-tolerated, it can interact with certain medications, particularly those metabolized by the liver. If you’re taking prescription medications, especially blood thinners, seizure medications, or medications with a grapefruit warning, consult with your healthcare provider before using CBD. This ensures safe and effective use alongside your current treatment plan.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
